    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@gakonst - I have created the following [PR](https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/pull/914). Alpine was giving me too many troubles when attempting to run `cast` and `forge` due to system dependencies. I also noticed some errors with `GLIBC` on `Centos` (`forge` requires version `2.29` and `centos` is only up to `2.28`). I decided to go with `debian` and everything works fine.\r\n\r\nA quick note on testing:\r\n* Prior to merging to master, I highly recommend manually running the pipeline to ensure that it publishes to dockerhub correctly.\r\n* You might need to update the `LABEL` in the `Dockerfile` as well as the `tag` in GHA to make everything work correctly.\r\n\r\nI hope this can get merged by Monday so I can use it in my current project :)\r\n\r\nThanks a lot, I am also currently working on running geth on a private network. This is a feature I am integrating from `dapptools`, I would be more than happy to discuss this with you guys and see if there is any interest in adding a \"tools\" section to foundry.\r\n\r\n- Cheers :) ",
